M||tx|---
M||titl|Parallel Nested Data Fetching
M||impa|ct
M||impa|eliminates server-side waterfalls
M||tags|server, rsc, parallel-fetching, promise-chaining
M||tx|---
M|Para|tx|When fetching nested data in parallel, chain dependent fetches within each item's promise so a slow item doesn't block the rest.
M|Para|**In|**
M|Para|tx|```tsx
M|Para|tx|const chats = await Promise.all(
M|Para|tx|chatIds.map(id => getChat(id))
M|Para|tx|)
M|Para|tx|const chatAuthors = await Promise.all(
M|Para|tx|chats.map(chat => getUser(chat.author))
M|Para|tx|)
M|Para|tx|```
M|Para|tx|If one `getChat(id)` out of 100 is extremely slow, the authors of the other 99 chats can't start loading even though their data is ready.
M|Para|**Co|**
M|Para|tx|```tsx
M|Para|tx|const chatAuthors = await Promise.all(
M|Para|tx|chatIds.map(id => getChat(id).then(chat => getUser(chat.author)))
M|Para|tx|)
M|Para|tx|```
M|Para|tx|Each item independently chains `getChat` → `getUser`, so a slow chat doesn't block author fetches for the others.